President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Vice Admiral Peter V. Neffenger as Assistant Secretary for the Transportation Security Administration (TSA) at the Department of Homeland Security. Neffenger has served as Vice Commandant of the U.S. Coast Guard since May 2014 and has more than three decades of experience in the Coast Guard. He has held various positions, including Deputy Commandant for Operations and Commander of the Ninth Coast Guard District. Neffenger has also served as Sector Commander and Federal Maritime Security Coordinator for the Ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach. He has received multiple degrees, including a B.A. from Baldwin Wallace University and an M.A. from the Naval War College.